Very hot- sunny- cry.  Water levels down 8-10 ".  No sun for weeks.
Several thunderstorms past week.  Cooler- sunny- light breeze.
Very hot.  87 F.  Bright haze.  Very light breeze.
Coolish.  Bright.  Light breeze.  Fluffy clouds.
Mostly sunny- calm winds- water levels about 2 inches high.
Partly cloudy day- calm winds- water about two inches high
Calm winds- slight hazy overcast- lake levels normal
Sunny day with cumulus clouds- wind from the North at 15 mph- lake with slight chop.
Clear with cumulus clouds- calm winds- sunny.
Hot- sunny day- calm winds- no clouds.
Calm winds- warm day- 60 degrees F.- high thin overcast- loons still here- algae on surface of calm bays.
Beautiful- sunny- warm spring day. Cloudless sky- with light wind from south at about 5 mph

Warm- sunny day with sparse small cumulus clouds. Wind from the south west at 5-10 mph. Air temp. about 68 F. Lake noticeably more clear than at my last recording. Fishing season opened last weekend. Very few boats on the water. Temperature sensor probably malfunctioning.
Winds calm- high overcast- generally sunny. Pine pollen beginning to be apparent on the lake. Water levels normal. Faithful spouse- Beverly- taking notes.
Hot- sunny day- no wind- clear sky- occasional cumulus clouds. Lake calm- but a lot of boat traffic- it being the 4th of July week.
Warm day- sunny with fluffy cumulus clouds- winds light from the SSE. Perfect day all around. Satellite overhead.
Again- a warm day. Partly cloudy with many fluffy cumulus clouds. Wind light from the south at about 5 mph. Satellite overhead.
Warm day again. Wind WNW at about 10mph. Mostly sunny. Slight chop on water. DNR expert instructing me on collection methods for phosphate and chlorophyll. All praise to Sandy Wichman.
Cloudless sky- wind SSW at about 10 mph- chop on water- sunny- but cool in wind.
Calm winds- mostly cloudy- numerous cumuli present. Boat traffic moderate. Mid 70's temps. Very pleasant day.
Wind SSW at about 5-10 mph- mostly sunny- pleasant day.
Cloud cover almost total- cool- light wind variable from the SSW. Rained after I got off the lake. Slight algae bloom present.

Partly cloudy with fluffy cumulus clouds against a blue sky.Winds NNW at about 5 mph. Air temperature about 55 F Fall color estimated at about 50%. An altogether beautiful day. Minor algal bloom present.
Very windy- 10-20 mph N/NW- moderate waves- sunny with few clouds.
Conditions on lake- 77 degrees air temperature- light wind from the S. about 0-5 mph. Partly sunny- slight chop on the water. Overall an excellent summer day.
Hot (90 degrees F )- wind SW at about 12 mph- water choppy- partially sunny. Nice to get out on the lake to help with the heat !

Partly sunny day- wind S. at about 5-10 mph. Slight chop on lake. About 70 degrees F. A fine day- light boat traffic with the exception of a boat pulling a tuber in circles for the duration of my sampling. Assistant- Porter the black Cocker Spaniel.
Partly sunny- cool at about 65 F. Wind NW at about 5-10 mph. Slight chop ong lake. Virtually no boats. Saw two breeding loon pairs yesterday. Surface temp. 68 F.
Clear sky with occasional small cumulus clouds- mostly sunny. Wind W. at 5-10 mph- slight chop to surface- no boats- loons calling. Surface temperature 68 F.
Mostly cloudy day- zero wind. Lake glassy. Surface temperature 76 F. Cloudy day- zero wind. Lake glassy.
Partly cloudy- wind SW at about 5 mph. Warm day- 72 F. Slight ripple on the water. Beautiful late summer day. Porter the dog assisting.

Sky  blue- clear- with few whispy chirrus clouds. Winds calm at 0-3 mph from the WSW. Slight ripple on the water. Beautiful day about 70 F. Water surface temperature 62 F. Porter the dog assisting. Wind shifting to the NNW during the sampling. Warm Autumn day- colors about 80-90%- yellow- orange- red- green.
Warmish Spring day- no wind- lake calm. Total cloud cover. Many loons this year- perhaps more than usual.
Overcast clouds- wind light at about 1-5 mph from the south- lake calm- loons sighted. Warm day- about 70 F. Porter the dog assisting.
Calm winds- 0-3 mph from the south-south/east- lake flat. Boaters out making waves. Partly cloudy- warm- temperature mid 60s. Porter the dog assisting.

Finally a warm day- with temps in the mid 70's. Very windy- 10-20 mph from south- southwest- lake very wavy. Mostly cloudy- sun breaks through occasionally. Recreational boats out with skiiers in spite of wind and waves. No sailboats out though- must be too windy for most. Porter the dog assisting.
Mostly cloudy- air temperature about 70 F. Wind 5-10 mph from the NNW. Lake with small waves. Sailboats out on the lake. Porter the dog assisting.

Warm- humid day- about 70 F. Wind from the north at 1-5 mph.- slight ripple on the lake. Total cloud cover. Many fishermen on the lake. Porter the dog assisting. Rain this AM and more on the way- we need it- dry August so far. Rainbow Reservoir down 3 ft.

Sunny day- temperature in the mid 60's- cool for a sunny August day. Looks to be a near record for the coolest summer recorded. Wind NNW at 0-5 mph- slight ripple on the lake as a result. Few boats out. Porter the dog assisting. Suspended algae present- but no algal scums noted.
Sky clear- NNW wind at 0-5 mph. Slight ripple on water. Beautiful day- 60-65 degrees F. Porter the dog and Bev assisting.

Totally clear sky- temperature about 50. No wind- lake like a mirror. Minor boat traffic.Fall color at peak- really beautiful. Porter the dog assisting. Algae dispursed in water and slight skims on shorelines. This will be my last sample for 2014- last bottle of lake water collected for color analysis. Next observation- ice on.

Clear blue sky with a few high chirrus clouds. Winds SSE at about 3-5 mph- with gusts to 10 mph. Lake with 2-3 inch ripples. No boats out. Heard many loons last night- saw one on lake during sampling time. Porter the dog assisting. Temperature low 60s.
Overcast skies with high cloud cover- wind 5 mph out of the SSW. ripples on water. Loons present- air temperature about 60 degrees. Porter the dog assisting.
Totally overcast day- winds South at 5 mph- 3 inch waves on lake. Heavy pine pollen on lake. Warm day- about upper 60s.
Fair amount of boat traffic today. Wind from the south at about 5 mph. Ripples and waves from boats present. Warm day- mid 70s- partly cloudy with puffy cumulus clouds and intermittant sun.
Wind NNE at 5-10 mph. Partly cloudy with puffy cumulus clouds. Slight wave action on lake. Ski boats evident.

Mostly sunny- calm winds or slight from the South- mostly calm water except for many water skiiers. Gulls again returned to the lake as they do every August. Puffy cumulus clouds with air temperature about 68 F. A very pleasant day. Porter the Dog assisting.
Mostly sunny- calm wind from the WNW at 0-5 mph. Small ripples on the lake. Beautiful day in the upper 50's.

column1: Cool temperatures have made an early turnover as indicated by the temperature/ dissolved oxygen readings.

column2: Total cloud cover- windy and cold- wind 5-10 mph from NNE. Six inch waves. Air temperature about upper 40s. Only one other boat on lake. No wildlife observed. Porter the dog assisting.
Sunny- blue sky. Moderate temperature about 63 degrees F. Slight wind N at 2-3 mph. Calm and quiet. Porter the dog assisting. Two boats on the lake. Amazing loon calls last night.
Partly sunny with cumulus clouds- winds variable WNW at 0-5 mph. Beautiful day- temperatures in the low 70's. Slight ripple on the surface. Porter the dog assisting.
Sunny with blue sky- few cumulus clouds. Wind S-SW at 5-10 mph- small waves on lake. Weather warm with temperature in the 80's. Spouse Beverly assisting.

Sunny and warm- 75-80 degrees F. Blue sky with puffy cumulus clouds. Winds calm to variable. Lake flat.- scarce boat traffic. Suspended particulate matter in water column- algae bloom beginning. Only slight at this time of  year. Porter the dog assisting.
Mostly cloudy day- wind WSW at 0-5 mph. Warm with temperatures about 70. Slight ripples on lake with scant boat traffic. Porter the Dog assisting.

Clear blue sky- wind South at 0-5 mph. Slight ripples on the water. Fishing boats nearby just off the deep hole. Air temperature low 60s- Fall colors not at peak yet- but close. Greater than average rainfall my be causing a later Fall color season. No appreciable algae bloom as yet.

Pleasant day- mostly sunny with puffy cumulus clouds in blue sky. Wind NW at 0-3 mph- slight ripple of waves on lake.Air temperature about 70 degrees Fahrenheit. Porter the dog assisting. Ski boats on lake. Nice day- air temperature about 70 degrees Fahrenheit. Winds slow at 0-3 mph from the NW- slight ripples on lake. Water ski boats out- blue sky with puffy cumulus clouds. First nice day after many days of rain. Porter the dog assisting.
Cloudless blue sky- wind 0-2 mph from S. Lake calm- ski boats on lake- slight ripple on water. Beverly and Porter assisting.

Still air- lake surface like a mirror. Blue sky with scattered small cumulus clouds. Air temperature 65-70 degrees F. Surface water temperature 69 degrees F. Beautiful day with Maples just beginning to turn yellow. Thin film of algae on water surface.
Warm day about 75 F.air temperature- wind 0-5 mph at NW- slight ripple on water. Some boat traffic. Mostly cloudy with cumulus present. Porter the Dog assisting.
Hot day- about 80 F- light S wind at 4 mph. Blue sky with scattered cumulus clouds. No boats on lake.
Calm winds- mostly sunny with scattered cumulus clouds. Slight ripple on water surface. Boat traffic present. 76 degrees F. in shade.

Another hot- sunny day with temperatures about 80 degrees F. Partly cloudy with puffy cumulus clouds present. Surface water temp.77 degrees F. Wind W.N.W. at 3-5 mph. Boat and jet ski traffic average. Porter the dog assisting.
Total cloud cover- gray day- wind SSW at 0-3 mph. Slight ripple on water- surface temperature of water 70 degrees F. Air temperature low 60s.
Sunny warm day with few scattered high clouds. Winds calm- lake flat. We've had unusually warm days for early September. No change of leaf color as yet. No boats on lake.
Mostly cloudy- wind SW at about 5 mph. Ripple on lake surface. Air temperature about 67 degrees F. Two boats on lake- both fishermen. Porter the Dog assisting. Loons heard nightly- also owls.
Warm day- about 79 degrees air temp. Clear day with cumulus clouds. Wind 5- 10 mph. from the S- SW- slight chop on surface of lake. Scientists Gus- Bev- and Fred on board. Great Summer day !
Partly cloudy- air temperature 73- wind SW at 5-10 mph- pleasant day on the lake. Beverly and Porter assisting.
Air temperature 66 F.- wind SE at 10-15 mph. Mostly cloudy. Few fishing boats on lakes. Porter the dog assisting. Moderate chop on surface.
Great day- sunny- blue sky with puffy cumulus clouds. Wind at 5 mph from West- lake with ripples- ski boats present. Surface water temperature 70.5 degrees F. Porter the dog assisting.

Beautiful day- Blue sky with cumulus clouds- wind light at 0-5 mph from the N.E. Surface water temperature 76.8 F. Many ski/tube boats on the lake- waves from boats present. Porter the dog and Beverly the spouse assisting.
Sunny with scattered cumulus clouds- variable winds 0-3 mph from the North. Lake calm. Surface water temp- 77.1 F. One boat on lake- Porter the Dog assisting- beautiful warm sunny day.
